reviews.text: If the Morikami Museum and Japanese Garden is not on your bucket list of places to visit in Florida, it should be. The art work is thought provoking and beautiful.  The Japanese garden is beautiful. There are walking trails and exhibitions where you can learn about the Japanese culture and the Japanese families that settled in the area. Everything is beautifully maintained and a great place to bring your family and friends. You can enjoy a nature walk, the cafeteria, the gift shop, or just sit on one of the many donated benches to enjoy the breeze and the beautiful landscape.

Lovely, serene place. For those with walking problems it is a hike to see the entire circle, especially on a hot day. There are, however, plenty of benches and the paths are pretty flat. If you don't have time or the inclination to walk all the way around the loop, head left out of the main building. There is a lovely waterfall right away on the left. On the next major peninsula, there is the original building with a nice history of the founder posted in it. Along with bathrooms and drinking fountains. Watch for iquanas and gold fish (by the old building). And sit a spell in silence and ponder the views or your navel! Small gift shop and usually an art exhibit in the main building. We heard the cafe was quite nice, but arrived too late to try it. Definitely recommend. Wear walking shoes a hat, and bring water and a camera!

Such a beautiful and serene place to spend the day or even a few hours. I took my time going through the gardens and honestly I wish I had the chance to spend more time. Every turn in the path was more beautiful and inspiring than the last. Definitely will come back again with more friends and also by myself

Very nice place at a very reasonable price.   We enjoyed a slow stroll through the gardens. We arrived later in the afternoon,  230-245, closed at 5 pm, we were done about 450 pm.  We were not sure if we were going to have enough time to see everything,  but we did.   Not may flowers were out as we visited after blooming.   Not sure what dates that would be,  but I'm sure it would have been alot more spectacular.  I would recommend this place if your looking to do something quite.

This is a very beautiful place to spend sometime at. It has a calming feel to it. Everyone in our group enjoyed themselves. The older as well as the young. Their restaurant had wonderful dishes for us to try. Next time we have company, we'll make sure to take them there.

The Seafood festival was an absolute blast! Parking wasn't a problem when you arrive early and decent there's a 4 hour maximum for parking.  The shopping was top shelf and I must say that law enforcement was respectable.

Doris was fabulous,  there were no parking information on the registrstion. That was terrible. I had to park 3 blocks away even though there was a policeman guiding traffic  was not enough to keep order. I was almost late.  I came from Pembroke Pines. I enjoy the presentation enormously.

Nice plaza. Great weekend concerts and activities. They need to add atleast one family friendly restaurant, so Mommy can have a cocktail and relax while the kids enjoy the ambient as well. Overall good experience.
Beautiful place. I was there with my husband to attend Boca Raton Fine Art Festival. It was a raining weekend but I enjoyed to walk few time around there. Beautiful stores and fantastic landscape.
Open air venue, free jazz brunch event with food & drink trucks, close-by free garage parking. Wonderful!

My wife and I split an order of spaghetti and meatballs incl garlic bread.  It was so delicious - perfect spices.  More than enough for two.  The meatballs were generous size and easy to split with a fork.  Can't wait to go back on our next trip from CT.

Went here on a whim and it was great. The portions you get for your money are HUGE. The pizza selection is insane--I had my first Baked Ziti PIZZA and I'm a big fan of white pizza and theirs was top notch. I was pleasantly surprised that the salad was very fresh, as well.

Food has always been great, service is admittedly loud sometimes, but they’re just energetic 😂. They always make sure I leave happy. The cashier Lola is so young but works like she owns the place! Forever a loyal customer.
The staff works so hard. Small restaurant that is always so busy & they do the best they can!! Always appreciate the food industry they try their best always!
I brought my friends here on a whim, and it was fantastic! The food was delicious, the service was great, and the atmosphere made for a great night. (Definitely suggest sitting outside 😉)

Wow just wow. Huge delicious portions at a good price. Super nice and fast service. Baby backs are yummy, tractor tread fries are crispy and taste great, and the Mississippi sweets are addictive! Our waitress was fabulous. So glad this place was recommended to us. Didn't stop eating to take pictures of food to post. To hungry and the food was way too yummy to waste a moment of food time.

I’ve been coming here on and off since I lived in Boca about 12 years. It’s been about three years since I’ve been in here. Place is still packed out the door but honestly I’m not impressed. I got the pulled pork sandwich which came with a few fries a good amount of pork and I got a piece of cornbread to go with it which was extra. First the pork was pretty dry.  Definitely not impressed. Cornbread was not moist either it was very gritty and kind of nasty. This place has gone way downhill in my opinion. Girl at the front was super nice and took good care of me. But the food to me is subpar. Honestly I could crush their barbecue in my backyard. I just Feel this place is totally dropped the ball. At least with the pulled pork. Pulled pork is much better from the tiny buffet at whole foods.

Ribs were really good. They finish them on a grill for that extra pop of flavor. The Carolina mustard sauce is unique and good as well. To finish dinner, I had the homemade key lime pie which was outstanding! Will be back next time I’m in the area!

Ate blackened catfish.  I was hoping for a healthy lunch, and the fish was great!  The portion was good sized.  They have some sweet potato chips that they fry in-house.  They were also quite good.  Sweet tea was almost as good as my grandma's.  :)

Ive been eating here for over 5 years and its always fresh, hot and delicious. I used to live in NC and this place has that country restaurant vibe and it's casual. The staff and service is always great. I recommend the wings and ribs combo plate with two sides. The Arnold Palmer iced teas are awesome too.
Awesome Pizza!  We come all the time.  It is so great to find a place that the adults and kids both enjoy equally.  We especially love their Sicilian.
It’s ALWAYS an amazing experience!!! The pizzas e pastas are A-M-A-Z-I-N-G!!! My family and I just love this place! Favorite ever!!! And the service is always just excellent!!!

Just tried my first pizza from here and it was awesome.  Tiny pizza joint with big taste.  Can't wait to try other menu items next time I come and visit my son who attends FAU.  The staff was very friendly and the place itself is nice and clean.  I also noticed the two American flags folded and proudly hung in their cases of two men one Koran War and one WWII with their photos on the wall.  Thank you to your family members service for our country and thank you for making our experience so great.  Keep up the great work.
I wouldnt pay 5 dollars for 1 slice of cheese pizza on lexington ave in Manhattan wouldnt do it in boca either
Best pizza I've been able to find in the area, really close to actual NY pizza. Prices are a bit high, but this is Boca so I can't complain.

Best Chinese in Boca. They just do it right here. small space but they do have dine in for 10-12 people and a sushi counter. Would recommend anyone who is looking to fill a chinese food want to try Kikis you won't be disappointed
The environment was awesome. John took care of us and definitely made me customers out of us
By far my most favorite Chinese food on the planet. Everything has flavor.
It was good so I went back and the same thing happen good food
Boneless ribs are to die for havent tried a dish here i havent liked
Super tasty Pad Thai! Great spot with really good lunch specials. Can't go wrong.

This is our second time here.
Really tasty food , good service.
We will be coming back again.

We saw good reviews, but our experience wasn't very good. The service was very slow and it was not that busy. They weren't open the first time we tried to go on a Saturday for lunch. I always order the same things at Thai restaurants because it's my favorite food and I was disappointed with the lack of flavor. Overall it wasn't horrible, but I'm not going back there.
Could be better. But still very good food.
This is a good place to  eat good food and very friendly  thank you.

Love their salad with gorgonzola added, a small is enough for two meals or two people! Love the eggplant, the large is more than twice the size of small but needs extra sauce. Pizza is irresistible although I like a little more cheese and sauce. Their food is addicting as nothing compares

The happy hour menu is great. The wings are $5 for 5 (normally $8) and a personal cheese pizza is $6 with $0.79 per topping added. Great deal for good food and the waitress was super friendly. Will be back again.

Following up to a PREVIOUS review. Tried to give Anthony's another shot, as location and curb side service are convenient. Pizza barely cooked. Never well done as advertised. Yet another dissapointment. Had to come home andput the pizza in our own oven. Not even a busy night for them. Such a shame. "Used to go here once a week. But the last couple of times we have been disappointed. The food quality has gone seriously downhill. The pizza is not cooked as much as it was in the past and is soggy and toppings have been sparse. Hope Management fixes this location soon."
Awesome food. Really love the thin-crusted pizza. Gives off an authentic italian feel 😎
Great place!  Love the atmosphere and the food!
Good prices, good food, good service. Great place to grab some quick Japanese food on your lunch break. All lunches come with soup and salad which is nice.

Great addition to the area. Awesome lunch specials for under $10. Everything I have tried over the last few weeks has been delicious and exceeded my expectations. And the staff is super friendly and sweet. So glad this spot opened!!!!
My favorite place to grab a fast lunch. Sushi quality is good and prices are unbeatable. Some of the servers do not speak the greatest English but hey welcome to south florida....

Worst hibachi I ever ate. Couldn't even finish my food, threw more than half of it in the garbage. Did not taste good, very bland, shrimp smelt fishy. Noodles and soup were tasteless. So disappointed and waste of my time and money. Waited one hour for food to go while other people came 15 minutes after, sat down and got their meals before me.
YOU CANT BEAT THE 9.95  LUNCH HIBACHI. STEAK, SOUP, EGG FRIED RICE, VEGGIES, SALAD AND IT CAN FEED 2 PEOPLE. I LOVE OISHI!!!

This was my first time coming to this place and let me tell you the food was really amazing . The eggplant parmigiana was insane . I ordered a salad for my meal and I was impressed. Not only was the food amazing . The customer service was over the top . The waitress that we had she was very attentive and from time to time would come to check on our table . The ambience was very inviting too. I will definitely come back ...

Oh my God this is the greatest hidden gem of the city.
The cashier / guy at the counter is super friendly. You place your order and they make food for you. That simple.
The dishes are other worldly. honestly I don't know, how they make such amazing dishes, but they're the best I've ever had. I would fly back to Boca Raton just for these amazing things. the ingredients are fresh and plentiful.

We randomly walked into Mario’s on a Friday afternoon, after visiting FAU. We could not have been happier with the food, the exceptionally friendly and professional staff, and the ambiance. Shawn took care of us at the outside bar and had great recommendations. Stacked eggplant app and grilled calamari app were amazing with White Haven Sauvignon. Happy Hour prices were a pleasant plus! Will definitely be back!

We went to Mario’s last night (2 couples) - my first time there. This is a large, busy restaurant- but the food and service were wonderful. I don’t eat pasta so they offered to substitute broccoli for me. The chicken tailgate was so good! Large portions and a fair price for what you get. We would go again!
Great food great  service. Gotta take advantage of the happy hour meals and drinks. Robbie is a good man

Are you kidding me? I called ahead for 12 people 5 of them being small kids. I had to wait another 45 minutes after the call ahead time to get seated and I repeat with 5 small children. Are you kidding me? Is the call ahead not done for that particular reason that I don’t have to spend an hour waiting for a table with small children? I don’t understand. The host not only is standing there giving me an issue but also making comments about how he can’t do anything. Perhaps you shouldn’t be making a call and head if you cannot accommodate. Disgusting! Very disappointed my last time here.

Excellent service that evening and the steaks were cooked to perfection. I strongly recommend people tell them to leave their seasoning off because it really ruins s a good piece of meat.  I loved that the sweet potato was not in foil so it was actually a sweet potato and not pudding.  The New York strip was amazingly tasty for the price. Our waiter was really on top of things and kept our glasses full and kept checking to see if we were satisfied. The salads were very fresh and tasty. I do recommend the wedge salad because it is excellent and a good value.

Wow Wow Wow. Had a great meal. Service was outstanding.  The waiter Michael was a step above all before.  We both had a special.  Lobster tail and Sirloin - and - Lobster tail and Crab Cakes and Shrimp skewer. A couple beers and the Awesome brownie.  Looking forward to going back and asking for the same waiter Michael!

I tried something new this visit and had the Pork Porterhouse. It was cooked perfectly, properly cooked and still juicy. It was very savory and I was very happy with my selection. The waiter, though he got our order correct and sufficiently attentive, while he was standing in front of our table seemed like we were keeping him from something more important. It was a typical Outback, so nothing to write home about with the decor. We were seating at the first booth from the lobby, so we saw quite a bit of foot traffic. In general, a nice meal with the delicious piece of pork being the best thing of the night.

Terrible experience yesterday. 3:45 in the afternoon and half the restaurant is empty! We were told to wait for 40 minutes until a waiter came on duty to wait on us🙄😡
So we left and went to Texas Roadhouse where we received amazing treatment with excellent customer service. 
We will not go back to Outback ever!!
My dad was the best chef in the world
Food was very good.  Service was good too.  This is a good value.  I live in West Palm Beach and this meal was worth the drive.  A1.  We will return.

I loved the atmosphere and their chicken wings were good! I also ordered the grilled salmon platter and it was delicious. Definitely will be coming back. It was only my first time, so I'm excited to try it out again.

I was looking for some good BBQ pulled pork to pick up for a co-worker's birthday/staff lunch at work.  I found Red's on google maps.  I'm glad I did!  The hush puppies and the pulled pork were a huge hit at the staff lunch!  Now, I just have to figure out how I can schedule our next staff lunch at Red's...

Imagine a BBQ joint that's run out of ribs at 1:00pm! No Baby Backs. Horrible service. Owner would not substitute St. Louis ribs for the Baby Back lunch special. What was served were tiny portions of greasy food. The BBQ chicken was baked and some generic sauce on top...not a hint of smoke. 

If you like real barbecue this is NOT the place  to go. Wonder how they stay in business?!

This place is awesome. Most importantly the team is fantastic and great service.
Food was amazing. Couldn't ask for a better place than this.
Recommended lobster rolls.
Will definitely be back here.
Great Japanese food in a beautiful hotel.  I got a chiraishi-don and a couple of hand rolls.

So fresh and delicious. We ordered the Fuji Omakasi and it was such a pleasure. The toro is to die for. Our server Boy and Fern were very accommodating and helped us order the most delicious Junmai premium sake. 
I’ll be back!

The food here was beyond our expectations and service from K. Orn was personal, friendly and professional. 
I've been here a few times before and was happy to come back. I can't believe thus place is still such a local secret.
Sushi was very high-quality although the price was too high to justify eating there over a place like Fuji
Staff is always very friendly and the wait is never bad. One of my absolute favorite places to get Pad Thai! Great experience overall.

reviews.author_name: Uri Rendon Owner, Pure Brokers LLC
reviews.text: I have to first say this place has good pricing, especially for the area. One of the sushi dishes was a bit watery (KC roll) and the liquid caused it to fall apart way too easily while being eaten. But overall the dish still tasted ok, which is why I rated 4/5. Everything else my friend and I had was really good. The dishes could have been laid out a little better but as you can see in my videos, they didn’t look terrible.

We haven't been here in years, maybe 15 but friends like it and wanted to go.

Pleasantly surprised at the selection and quality of food.
I started with the Sunomono ,octopus, conch, krab, masago, scallion & cucumber over seaweed salad, very good. My wife ordered her favorite, Tom Kha Kai ,Thai coconut soup with chicken, mushroom, scallion, and bell pepper. She said it was the best she has ever had.

For mains, i had the Deluxe Sashimi , assortment of raw fish including conch & octopus, Came with either soup or salad. Amazing presentation (see the picture). Nice selection of fresh fish. My wife ordered the K.C Roll ,salmon, krab, cream cheese, avocado asparagus, masago, scallion wrapped in cucumber with ponzu sauce.
She loved it.

Definitely will return.

Good food and good service
Friendly / Manerger so nice and friendly
Once a week. My favorite business lunch stop in Boca. Great food. Nice staff. Get's me in and out guickly knowing my short, late lunch break.

Delicious, fresh Mediterranean/Greek food with a fun staff. Indoor or outdoor seating.  They have a fun belly dancer for entertainment and.you can join in if you please! Belly dancer Fri/Sat after 8pm

After my visit I must say this is my favorite Greek Restaurant in Boca. I am 100% Greek so I really know what good authentic Greek food should taste like. The service is phenomenal and the food is so tasty and flavorful. It truly reminds me of my YiaYai's (Grandma's) food that she cooks me from scratch in Greece. It makes me so proud to be Greek and I am so pleased how this restaurant gives Floridians a taste of Greece.

First time customer and I highly recommend Taverna Kyma as a must try! The service was amazing was delicious and the food was so authentic, I had the lamb burger with salad and fries, meanwhile my co workers enjoyed the chicken skewers and gyro! The bar was beautiful and the scenery was authentic feeling as well! Will definitely be back!

The food is very very good and so is the service. HOWEVER the noise level is higher than in a nightclub. When the place is full the acoustics make it so that you have to practically shout to the person next to you to have a conversation. Not only that but they play music over the soundsystem at nightclub level. It actually is loud enough to damage your hearing. We asked them to turn the music down which they never did and actually turned it up louder. I would never go to eat there again. Maybe get takeout or sit on the patio if they have a table available because the food is delicious but I would rather put a spike in my head than sit through another meal there.  I don't understand that mentality of making the place so noisy. A big part of going out to eat is enjoying the food and conversation. How can you do that when you are in a meat grinder of noise?

I usually order to go and the food is always excellent! Tonight was my first time dinning in. They tried to sit us in a dark corner in an area where no one else was sitting (take a wild guess what color my husband is -_-), which I didn't like and asked to be moved. **note that tables were open all around amongst the other diners there** Once we were moved we met our waiter who seemed nice but once he took our order, he disappeared for the rest of the night. Never checked on us, we didn't get refills on our drinks, and once we were ready to go we sat for about 10 min. until we finally called out to another waiter to give us to-go boxes and our check. I would like to think that this was a fluke and maybe an emergency came up but we saw our waiter as we were leaving. He didn't say a word. I'm so sad because I work in the area and order from here. I bragged about this place to my husband and he wasn't impressed. They let me down 😑. Moral of the story... food is great but you have to choose between your morals or your stomach.

Chops Lobster Bar offers several ways to enjoy its food and drink. The one we shared with a good friend was the Happy Hour on the veranda next to the sidewalk. A variety of small plates are on offer for reasonable prices. Cut-price drinks complement the Happy Hour fare. Shane was our delightful server.

OMG.. my favorite happy hour hands down. The atmosphere is elegant and I love the round red booths. I always get the crab cake or the lobster roll. The drinks are good too. The service is a 4 not a 5. I made a simple request twice and twice I was blew off.

Had the 3 course dinner. 8 of us at a lovely round table. Waiter was a bit too eager to "sell up" the pricey menu items & crab leg seafood app tower.( I find that annoying as he knew one party was picking up the entire check.) Chopped salad was good, fried lobster tail was good, dessert of berries and the chocolate cake dessert were good, but the steak was disappointing.
Ruth's Chris steaks are much better. Atmosphere is cozy and you can have a conversation which is very nice. I would return, but would not order a steak there again. Perhaps they provide a lesser quality steak with the 3 course dinner to keep their costs down.

Excellent steaks and sides. Very good wines by the glass with generous pour. Service excellent. Somewhat noisy. Only disappointment was bread, but we were told they had a problem with onion roll delivery. Nonetheless, we had a very nice evening, and great steaks. Will return.
One of the best spots in the area. I had a brother come into town and he asked me to go back here. They have so many good reviews for a reason.

We went here not too long ago and the steak was the best we have had in Boca by far!  The service is amazing, the steaks were cooked to perfection, and the drinks were incredible.  The perfect date night!
Great atmosphere and very friendly staff, their prices aren't outrageous like some places. But most importantly their food is amazing!! Their steaks are always fresh.

Went to NY Prime with my parents and my girlfriends parents. Went in the night of 12/23. I will start off by sayin my rib-eye was fantastic and perfectly cooked! Now for the not so great. As I walked up to the restaurant I couldn’t help but head tires screeching in the parking lot from a car driving way too fast, turns out it was a valet in a customers car, he’s lucky it was not mine! I reported this to the gal up front who offered genuine concern.  Our server seemed generally annoyed by my parents, granted they annoy me too, but the server should have a little more patience. After I mentioned that to him he seemed a bit better. The sides are mediocre at best. The dessert was tasty. I think for what they are trying to be they are currently missing the mark.
One of my favorite places to dine in Boca! I especially love their Ladies Night on Wednesdays! Great live entertainment and always amazing food!
Very good service. Excellent food. I ordered the Filet Mignon medium rare it was delicious and well cooked.  The shrimp as appetizers I recommend it.

Been awhile since the wife and I dined here. Last time was a great experience and this time as well.  Filet was perfect, sweet potato casserole to die for.  Everyone made my wife's birthday celebration wonderful. Even parked my car up front even though I don't drive a Ferrari... Would recommend this place to anyone, and have....

The food was good. In my mind, service was below average. Had a large party and just not up to the standards of a steakhouse of this level. 

Coffee served after desert, no creamer on table. The server poured it from a container into peoples cups directly.  Utensils for desert not provided until after desert was served. When I asked about silverware, server told me they are behind me. Main course served on small plate, no room for "family style sides" on plate. No extra plate provided. 

Drinks were brought slowly. When taking orders the server started with me. As the host of the party I wanted her to take my guests order first and suggested this. It was a problem for her and she said as much. 

Table was not completely cleared between courses. There were extra glasses left on the table. 

Overall poor service.

However the party planner Jamie was fantastic to work with. Very accommodating, pleasant and efficient.
The chef really really did a wonderful job. My rib eye and lobster was 😋! And the waiter did an over the top job with ensuring I got everything I asked for. Highly recommended
A favorite evening place of mine. The place has an awesome atmosphere. Atmosphere and food reminds me of Virginia Beach.
Service was amazing from the start, valet was professional and service was beyond expectations. Best steakhouse in the area.

The ambiance is sophisticated and festive. The servers are professional and knowledgeable, attentive without hovering. The food is incredible. I haven't eaten here for a few years, so I was delighted to find new dishes on the menu. My meal was perfectly seasoned and plated. I will eat here again!

Very romantic place for a random husband and wife date night. Our server was very knowledgeable and on top of his game. The food was amazing, we had an absolutely lovely time! Would def go back again to this location.

This restaurant greets you as an old friend.  Friendly, happy to answer any questions and polite.  Amanda was our waitress.  She was just perfect.  She anticipated our needs and was very attentive.   The food is out of this world.  From the stuffed mushrooms to the filet with caramelized scallops, the dining experience is the best. We will be back every time we visit our children.

To

Just enjoyed a wonderful meal with my girlfriend for a late valentines dinner. Our server Antonio had excellent recommendations for whiskey and food! Great place to go for a nice meal without totally breaking the bank! Thanks Antonio!

PHENOMENAL!!!

Scallops were incredible. Highly recommend! Request Matthew as your server, best service I have received in a long time.

The crisp beef is really good. Friends were staying at the Marriott which is located in the same Plaza where this restaurant is. Nice restaurant. Service was good they even have a bar  My dad's friends from out of town had a great time!

Lousy service, owner Howard is a cheap individual. The order didn’t have no sauce and had the wrong stuff in it and when we asked to fix it, he didn’t do it. Nobody should ever go to the restaurant again - very poor service and lousy waiters

Acceptable; not amazing. Americanized upscale Chinese with a few less common items to round out the menu. Service was perfectly fine. Rice was excellent  (I'm a rice snob); crispy beef was uninspired; tofu vegetable soup had good variety and quality vegetables.

Food allergies? Don’t go. My wife has severe food allergies and requested plain steamed shrimp with garlic on the side. The waitress said they wouldn’t do it. We asked to speak with the owner and he came to the table. Even though the menu clearly says they will accommodate food allergies he flat out refused. “We don’t serve garlic on the side”he said. My wife very calmly explained that she was following her doctors instructions. The owners response to that was, and I’m quoting. “I don’t care what the doctor tells you.” 

With that we just left. The restaurant was 3/4’s empty at the height of the tourist season and we know know why. Highly recommend you stay away.
My favorite restaurant. They serve one delicious dish after another. I often travel all the way from County Line Rd to get a bite here. They serve food you can't live without.
